name: 尤金·帕帕利亚
name_full: 尤金·帕帕利亚 Eugenio Papalia
introduction: Eugenio Papalia was born in 1990. After moving to Rome, he graduated from Silvio d'Amico National Academy of Dramatic Arts. During an intense phase of working in theater, playing main character roles on stage, he started collaborating with many tv and cinema productions as well. In tv, he debuted in 2017 in the series "Squadra Antimafia '' and, in cinema, in Alessandro Pondi's film "Chi m'ha visto". In the following year he obtained a small role in the series "La Porta Rossa" directed by Carmine Elia.
